From: Benjamin 
Sent: Tuesday, March 7, 2023 8:49 AM
Subject: RE: Landa- Electrical requirements - RFI - RESPONSE
 
Hi all,
 
See response from Electrician below:
Proposed Phase arrangement:
A Phase – 3 Units
B Phase – 3 Units
C Phase – 4 Units
House Power – Uses all 3 phases.
 
Knowing this, Lighting Maximum Demand is 6 amps per phase as per Table C1, (a)(i) column 3 of AS/NZS3000:2017
 
For Example, if we had a total of 18 units (6 units per phase) we would need to refer to column 4. Which would equate to:  5 + (0.5 x 6)= 8amps per phase.
So 24amps is completely overkill. (For E.g. 24amps is equal to 552 x 10watt LED downlights)
Next we have the Ovens, cooktops are not included in our calculations as they purely activate the igniter within the cooktop which is a neglible amount amount power.
 
Based on 3 or 4 units per phase, Ovens are calculated at 15amps per phase as per Table C1, (c) Column 3 of AS/NZS3000:2017
 
For Example, if we had a total of 18 units (6 units per phase) we would need to refer to column 4. Which would equate to:  2.8 x 6 = 16.8amps per phase.
So 38 amps per phase is clearly incorrect, this is basically a full load calculation. (9.6amps x 4 = 38.4amps)

 
Thanks
